Ida Adams https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ida_Adams 0 Ida Adams (c. 1888 – November 4, 1960), sometimes credited as Ida M. Adams, was an American-born actress and singer who worked chiefly in musical theatre. Her career from 1909 to 1914 was in the United States, then in London's West End from 1915 to 1917. Adams also wrote the story on which the silent film Limousine Life (1918) starring Olive Thomas was based.
